==English==

===Etymology===
From Greek ''alpha'' (''άλφα''), the first letter of the [[Greek]] [[alphabet]], from the [[Phoenician]] ''[[aleph]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈæɫfə/}}
* {{audio|en-us-alpha.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# The name of the first letter of the Greek alphabet ('''[[Α]]''', &nbsp;'''[[α]]'''), followed by [[beta]]. In the Latin alphabet it is the predecessor to '''A'''.
# {{science}} The name of the [[symbol|symbols]] '''Α''' and '''α''' used in science and mathematics, often interchangeable with the symbols when used as a prefix.
#:: ''I will attempt to make a '''alpha''' particle ("α-particle") with the large hadron collider.''
# {{finance}} The return of a given asset or portfolio adjusted for [[systematic risk]].

